Visualization 1: GDP¶

In [5]:
# get most recent year of data for each country
df_1 = df_1.sort_values('year', ascending=False).groupby('country').first()
df_1 = df_1[df_1['year'] >= 2010]
df_1.shape
Out[5]:
(159, 54)
In [6]:
# get geopandas data and merge 
world = geopandas.read_file(geopandas.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
world.columns=['pop_est', 'continent', 'country', 'c3', 'gdp_md_est', 'geometry'] # change to "c3" so we can align code
merge_1=pd.merge(world, df_1,on='c3')
merge_1.shape
Out[6]:
(141, 59)
In [7]:
merge_1.plot(column='gdp_ppp_pc_usd2011', scheme="quantiles",
           figsize=(25, 20),
           legend=True,cmap='coolwarm')
plt.title('Most Recently Reported GDP (Based on Purchasing Power Parity) in Different Countries',fontsize=25)
plt.show()
